metadata.name: 臥竜鳳雛 - Garyohosu
metadata.description:
臥竜鳳雛 - Garyohosu is a Yojijukugo (Four Kanji Idiom)

臥竜 - Garyo: A prostrate dragon
鳳雛 - Hosu: A phoenix chick
These words refer to "an outstanding person who is not yet known to the world" and "a young man with a very promising future", respectively.

I gave this title to the samurai in hopes to make him known, similarly, with the hope that my work would also make a leap to the world.

*For Yojijukugo, please see the description of this collection.

*Size: 44.7MB (5184 x 6912)
